WEBVTT

1
00:00:09.009 --> 00:00:12.554
- (BUZZ SAW SCREECHING)
- ♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

2
00:00:16.475 --> 00:00:18.101
(DOG GROWLING)

3
00:00:21.855 --> 00:00:23.357
(SNARLS. HUFFS)

4
00:00:32.866 --> 00:00:34.826
♪ (MUSIC RISES) ♪

5
00:00:34.910 --> 00:00:37.663
(ZOMBIE SNARLS. GROANS)

6
00:00:38.997 --> 00:00:41.041
♪ (MUSIC INTENSIFIES) ♪

7
00:00:52.010 --> 00:00:53.720
- Hey. Stuart.
- ♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

8
00:00:53.804 --> 00:00:54.972
Bert.

9
00:00:55.055 --> 00:00:56.557
Got anything new?

10
00:00:57.808 --> 00:00:58.892
Funny every time.

11
00:00:58.976 --> 00:01:01.770
(PORTAL HISSES. WARBLES)

12
00:01:01.853 --> 00:01:04.731
I think I'm ready to pull
the trigger on <i>Batman 608.</i>

13
00:01:05.732 --> 00:01:07.442
Excellent choice.

14
00:01:08.026 --> 00:01:09.194
What's the trade?

15
00:01:09.278 --> 00:01:12.823
What would you say
to a can of lima beans?

16
00:01:12.906 --> 00:01:16.159
Oh. geez. Bert. come on!
This is near mint.

17
00:01:16.201 --> 00:01:18.787
I could probably get a couple
Dinty Moore Beef Stews for this.

18
00:01:18.870 --> 00:01:20.080
Plus...

19
00:01:20.872 --> 00:01:22.332
cream corn.

20
00:01:22.416 --> 00:01:23.834
- Meh.
- BERT KIBBLER: Okay.

21
00:01:23.875 --> 00:01:27.087
I was saving it for my birthday.
but I guess I'll throw it in.

22
00:01:28.088 --> 00:01:29.590
Fancy Feast.

23
00:01:30.382 --> 00:01:31.341
What flavor?

24
00:01:31.425 --> 00:01:33.010
- Salmon.
- Sold.

25
00:01:33.093 --> 00:01:35.178
- Yay!
- TREVOR: Um. are you crazy?

26
00:01:35.262 --> 00:01:37.639
(SCOFFS) Hawkeye doesn't deserve
to be an Avenger.

27
00:01:37.723 --> 00:01:39.850
Yeah-- Whoa. whoa. whoa. whoa!
You do not want to go there.

28
00:01:39.891 --> 00:01:41.643
You got a guy
with a bow and arrow.

29
00:01:41.727 --> 00:01:43.353
and he's supposed to be
on the same team

30
00:01:43.395 --> 00:01:45.939
as a guy
with an arc reactor iron suit

31
00:01:46.023 --> 00:01:47.441
and the literal God of Thunder?

32
00:01:47.524 --> 00:01:49.109
(LAUGHS) What sense
does that even make?

33
00:01:49.192 --> 00:01:52.696
I don't know. I mean... (GRUNTS)
...does this make sense?

34
00:01:52.779 --> 00:01:55.657
- (SCREAMS. GROANS)
- ♪ (UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

35
00:01:55.699 --> 00:01:59.911
I just mopped!
We talked about this. Kyle!

36
00:01:59.995 --> 00:02:01.246
That's strike three!

37
00:02:01.330 --> 00:02:03.624
I'm sorry. okay?
Uh. but you heard him.

38
00:02:05.667 --> 00:02:07.502
Sorry. He started it.

39
00:02:08.337 --> 00:02:09.379
Unbelievable.

40
00:02:09.421 --> 00:02:11.673
- Give me a hand.
- BERT: Oh. yeah.

41
00:02:11.715 --> 00:02:14.551
You know. I feel the same way
about Green Arrow.

42
00:02:14.635 --> 00:02:16.970
Yeah. we all do but you don't
have to kill people.

43
00:02:17.554 --> 00:02:20.223
(PORTAL HISSES. WARBLES)

44
00:02:20.265 --> 00:02:22.059
(SIGHS) Bye!

45
00:02:22.100 --> 00:02:24.102
You ever wonder
where this thing goes?

46
00:02:24.186 --> 00:02:25.312
Nope.

47
00:02:25.395 --> 00:02:27.606
- Probably smart.
- TRAVELER: Stuart.

48
00:02:27.689 --> 00:02:29.733
♪ (INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

49
00:02:29.775 --> 00:02:30.984
We gotta talk.

50
00:02:32.778 --> 00:02:34.738
Shit just got weird.

51
00:02:34.780 --> 00:02:38.408
♪ (THEME SONG PLAYING) ♪

52
00:02:39.284 --> 00:02:42.079
<i>♪ Stuart tries
To reset our lives ♪</i>

53
00:02:42.120 --> 00:02:45.415
<i>♪ But he fails
To save the universe ♪</i>

54
00:02:45.457 --> 00:02:48.585
<i>♪ He's our only chance
And he tries and he tries ♪</i>

55
00:02:48.627 --> 00:02:51.838
<i>♪ But he fails
To save the universe ♪</i>

56
00:02:53.173 --> 00:02:57.260
♪ (CHOIR VOCALIZING) ♪

57
00:03:05.185 --> 00:03:08.438
<i>♪ Stuart fails ♪</i>

58
00:03:08.522 --> 00:03:11.441
♪ (THEME SONG CONCLUDES) ♪

59
00:03:11.525 --> 00:03:13.360
Do you have
an identical twin brother?

60
00:03:13.443 --> 00:03:15.112
- ♪ (SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- No.

61
00:03:15.153 --> 00:03:16.947
- Okay. I have two questions.
- Just two?

62
00:03:17.030 --> 00:03:18.949
I've only got a few seconds
to explain this.

63
00:03:18.990 --> 00:03:20.117
so you gotta focus.

64
00:03:20.158 --> 00:03:22.202
- Who are you?
- First question.

65
00:03:22.285 --> 00:03:24.996
I'm you from
another stream of reality.

66
00:03:25.080 --> 00:03:27.499
Well. that answers that.
Second question...

67
00:03:27.582 --> 00:03:29.292
Listen to me.

68
00:03:29.334 --> 00:03:32.629
This apocalyptic nightmare
that you are living in.

69
00:03:32.671 --> 00:03:34.965
it can be avoided.
it never has to happen.

70
00:03:35.006 --> 00:03:37.300
Okay. now I have.
like. six questions.

71
00:03:37.384 --> 00:03:39.553
- He can't be me.
- He looks like you.

72
00:03:39.636 --> 00:03:42.514
Senior prom. Emily Manhart.
peach schnapps.

73
00:03:42.597 --> 00:03:44.474
She was ready to go.
You puked in her lap.

74
00:03:44.558 --> 00:03:45.809
Sounds like you.

75
00:03:45.892 --> 00:03:47.352
At least I went
to my senior prom.

76
00:03:47.436 --> 00:03:49.771
I couldn't go. I had mono.

77
00:03:49.855 --> 00:03:51.690
Please. I don't have
a lot of time.

78
00:03:51.773 --> 00:03:54.484
Leonard Hofstadter.
Sheldon Cooper. Howard Wolowitz.

79
00:03:54.568 --> 00:03:56.820
- Remember them?
- Yeah. real nerds.

80
00:03:56.903 --> 00:03:58.155
Pot-kettle.

81
00:03:58.196 --> 00:03:59.865
- Sure.
- Fair enough.

82
00:03:59.948 --> 00:04:04.953
Anyway. they invented some kind
of quantum entanglement thing.

83
00:04:04.995 --> 00:04:06.830
and you were there
when it malfunctioned.

84
00:04:06.913 --> 00:04:08.123
Both of us or just him?

85
00:04:08.206 --> 00:04:10.250
- Doesn't matter!
- It matters to me.

86
00:04:10.333 --> 00:04:12.377
The point is.
it altered reality.

87
00:04:12.461 --> 00:04:14.045
None of this is supposed to be.

88
00:04:14.129 --> 00:04:16.506
And by none of this.
you mean...?

89
00:04:16.590 --> 00:04:17.632
None of it!

90
00:04:18.884 --> 00:04:23.430
The violence. the devastation.
the dimensional rifts!

91
00:04:23.513 --> 00:04:26.391
- Dimensional rifts!
- Now we know.

92
00:04:26.475 --> 00:04:28.727
None of this is normal.

93
00:04:31.229 --> 00:04:33.356
- Certainly not that!
- The big moth?

94
00:04:33.440 --> 00:04:36.526
(SCOFFS) Yes! Yes! The big moth!

95
00:04:36.610 --> 00:04:39.070
If you turn the lights off.
they don't bother you.

96
00:04:40.864 --> 00:04:43.450
You can put everything right.
You can make it the way it was.

97
00:04:43.533 --> 00:04:45.452
- You just have to find the--
- Hang on.

98
00:04:45.535 --> 00:04:46.995
- Hang on!
- ♪ (INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

99
00:04:47.037 --> 00:04:49.289
If you're me
from another reality.

100
00:04:49.372 --> 00:04:50.916
how can you be in this one?

101
00:04:50.999 --> 00:04:53.043
I don't know.
I'm not a quantum physicist.

102
00:04:53.084 --> 00:04:54.878
I went to the Rhode Island
School of Design.

103
00:04:54.920 --> 00:04:57.297
- I didn't know that.
- Oh. yeah. I have a BFA.

104
00:04:57.380 --> 00:04:59.549
Really? How come
you never did anything with it?

105
00:04:59.591 --> 00:05:01.009
What am I gonna do.
teach high school kids

106
00:05:01.092 --> 00:05:03.595
- how to draw fruit?
- (SIGHS) Guys. please!

107
00:05:03.678 --> 00:05:06.556
The machine is still at Caltech.
Here's what you have to do.

108
00:05:06.640 --> 00:05:08.266
Hang on. let me write this down.

109
00:05:08.350 --> 00:05:10.769
♪ (QUIRKY SUSPENSEFUL
MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

110
00:05:10.852 --> 00:05:12.521
"Cal... "

111
00:05:12.604 --> 00:05:14.231
Oh. shoot!

112
00:05:14.272 --> 00:05:17.400
- What is shaking it gonna do?
- Stop talking and listen.

113
00:05:17.484 --> 00:05:19.945
You know. I might have
a Sharpie. excuse me.

114
00:05:21.279 --> 00:05:23.907
- Listen!
- ♪ (DRAMATIC MUSICAL STING) ♪

115
00:05:23.990 --> 00:05:25.492
When you get to the machine...

116
00:05:25.575 --> 00:05:27.994
- (GARBLED SPEECH)
- ♪ (MYSTERIOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

117
00:05:28.078 --> 00:05:29.788
- Damn it!
- W... What's happening?

118
00:05:29.871 --> 00:05:30.914
I don't know!

119
00:05:30.997 --> 00:05:33.667
I'm going through
some kind of wormhole!

120
00:05:33.750 --> 00:05:36.336
(GROANS)
The important thing is...

121
00:05:36.419 --> 00:05:39.673
(GARBLED SPEECH)

122
00:05:39.756 --> 00:05:41.842
And... And when you find him...

123
00:05:41.925 --> 00:05:43.677
(GARBLED SPEECH)

124
00:05:44.845 --> 00:05:47.764
...and that will fix everything.

125
00:05:47.848 --> 00:05:50.141
(WHOOSHING WARBLE)

126
00:05:52.435 --> 00:05:54.396
You get any of that?

127
00:05:54.479 --> 00:05:56.815
- I got the gist.
- ♪ (MUSIC FADES) ♪

128
00:05:56.898 --> 00:05:58.650
- ♪ (INTENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- (DOG BARKING)

129
00:05:58.733 --> 00:06:00.777
(BARKS. GROWLS)

130
00:06:00.861 --> 00:06:02.737
(GROWLS. SNARLS)

131
00:06:02.821 --> 00:06:04.114
- (WANDERER GRUNTS)
- (TEETH CRUNCH)

132
00:06:04.197 --> 00:06:05.282
(DOG WHIMPERS)

133
00:06:05.323 --> 00:06:06.992
Nice catch. Steve!

134
00:06:07.075 --> 00:06:08.660
How is it out there?

135
00:06:08.743 --> 00:06:11.079
It's a little nippy.
Wear layers.

136
00:06:11.162 --> 00:06:13.081
- (DOOR RATTLES)
- (KEYS JANGLING)

137
00:06:14.165 --> 00:06:15.250
Shall we?

138
00:06:15.333 --> 00:06:19.129
(SIGHS) Mm. I don't know.
I'm having second thoughts.

139
00:06:19.170 --> 00:06:21.923
What are you talking about?
We've been given a quest.

140
00:06:22.007 --> 00:06:23.967
Yeah. but. uh.
do we believe that guy?

141
00:06:24.009 --> 00:06:25.302
That guy was you.

142
00:06:25.385 --> 00:06:26.344
That's my point.

143
00:06:26.428 --> 00:06:28.805
When did we start listening
to me?

144
00:06:28.847 --> 00:06:31.308
Maybe we have a chance
to fix the world.

145
00:06:31.349 --> 00:06:33.226
I don't know.
I think it's important
to ask the question.

146
00:06:33.310 --> 00:06:35.186
Is this reality that bad?

147
00:06:35.270 --> 00:06:36.396
(ZOMBIE GROWLS)

148
00:06:36.479 --> 00:06:37.397
(ZOMBIE GROANS)

149
00:06:37.480 --> 00:06:39.482
I think there's room
for improvement.

150
00:06:39.524 --> 00:06:43.695
♪ (FUNKY TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

151
00:06:44.863 --> 00:06:48.617
(SCAVENGERS GRUNTING)

152
00:06:49.367 --> 00:06:50.952
What are you doing?

153
00:06:51.036 --> 00:06:53.288
What's it look like?
I'm trying to get us to Caltech.

154
00:06:53.371 --> 00:06:55.165
With a Thomas Guide?

155
00:06:55.206 --> 00:06:57.709
I would've used
the GPS on my iPhone.

156
00:06:57.792 --> 00:07:00.003
but civilization
seemed to have collapsed.

157
00:07:00.045 --> 00:07:01.504
- (RAT SQUEALS. CHOMPS)
- PENN: Ow!

158
00:07:01.588 --> 00:07:02.756
Check it out.

159
00:07:02.839 --> 00:07:04.758
♪ (JAUNTY CARNIVAL MUSIC
PLAYING OVER SPEAKERS) ♪

160
00:07:04.841 --> 00:07:06.009
- Juggling two-- (YELPS)
- (RAT CHOMPS)

161
00:07:06.092 --> 00:07:09.554
Juggling two starving
feral creatures.

162
00:07:09.638 --> 00:07:12.182
as. uh. you can see.
is not difficult. but...

163
00:07:12.265 --> 00:07:13.516
- (RATS SQUEALING. CHOMPING)
- (GROANS)

164
00:07:13.600 --> 00:07:18.563
...juggling three is... (GRUNTS)
...profoundly stupid. Ow!

165
00:07:18.647 --> 00:07:19.898
(GRUNTS)

166
00:07:19.981 --> 00:07:21.733
I saw them in Vegas.

167
00:07:21.816 --> 00:07:23.610
- Such a fun night.
- Oh.

168
00:07:23.693 --> 00:07:26.529
You know who I loved in Vegas
and I didn't think I would?

169
00:07:26.571 --> 00:07:28.323
- Huh?
- Celine Dion.

170
00:07:28.406 --> 00:07:30.575
Mm. Oh. I'm sorry.

171
00:07:30.659 --> 00:07:33.745
- (RATS SQUEALING)
- (PENN GRUNTS. GROANS)

172
00:07:36.247 --> 00:07:37.248
Oh. all right.

173
00:07:38.500 --> 00:07:40.001
- (RAT CHOMPS)
- (GROANS) Yeah.

174
00:07:40.085 --> 00:07:41.962
(GRUNTS)

175
00:07:44.923 --> 00:07:46.216
(EXHALES)

176
00:07:46.299 --> 00:07:47.342
Thank you!

177
00:07:47.425 --> 00:07:49.010
- We are Penn and Teller...
- (AUDIENCE APPLAUDING)

178
00:07:49.094 --> 00:07:51.388
...and we'll be here
until we're dead!

179
00:07:51.471 --> 00:07:53.431
- (RATS SQUEALING)
- (PENN GRUNTS)

180
00:07:53.515 --> 00:07:56.267
- (FLIES BUZZING)
- ♪ (DARK TECHNO MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

181
00:07:56.351 --> 00:08:00.063
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

182
00:08:00.146 --> 00:08:01.815
(PORTAL HISSES. WARBLES)

183
00:08:08.029 --> 00:08:10.740
- Moth.
- (CROWD GASPING)

184
00:08:10.824 --> 00:08:13.743
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

185
00:08:13.827 --> 00:08:17.580
Oh. my God. look. Floss.

186
00:08:17.664 --> 00:08:19.582
BERT: Just hurry.
It's getting dark.

187
00:08:19.666 --> 00:08:20.750
STUART BLOOM: Yeah. yeah. yeah.

188
00:08:20.792 --> 00:08:23.753
Excuse me. uh. how much
for a foot of floss?

189
00:08:23.795 --> 00:08:26.047
- Mint or regular?
- Uh. let me get the regular.

190
00:08:26.131 --> 00:08:27.090
VENDOR: Oh.

191
00:08:27.132 --> 00:08:29.259
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

192
00:08:29.342 --> 00:08:32.846
♪ (INTRIGUING MUSICAL STING) ♪

193
00:08:32.929 --> 00:08:35.557
Thank you.
Oh. yeah. look at that.

194
00:08:36.391 --> 00:08:38.351
Can't put a price
on healthy gums.

195
00:08:41.104 --> 00:08:43.940
Oh! Oh. this feels so good.

196
00:08:43.982 --> 00:08:45.984
Go easy. We're sharing that.

197
00:08:46.818 --> 00:08:47.986
(GUN COCKS)

198
00:08:48.778 --> 00:08:49.904
Not a good sound.

199
00:08:53.158 --> 00:08:54.409
Stuart?

200
00:08:55.910 --> 00:08:56.953
Denise?

201
00:08:56.995 --> 00:08:58.413
I thought you were dead.
(CHUCKLES)

202
00:08:58.496 --> 00:09:00.832
- I thought you were dead!
- Aw!

203
00:09:00.915 --> 00:09:03.126
So. what have you been up to?

204
00:09:03.209 --> 00:09:04.294
Robbing mostly.

205
00:09:04.377 --> 00:09:05.628
Still working on my screenplay.

206
00:09:05.712 --> 00:09:07.839
- Oh. good for you.
- Yeah. How have you been?

207
00:09:07.922 --> 00:09:10.508
- Okay. Still got the store.
- Oh. that's great.

208
00:09:10.592 --> 00:09:12.218
What's going on?

209
00:09:12.302 --> 00:09:13.803
Don't worry. Gary.
I know these guys.

210
00:09:13.887 --> 00:09:15.346
So. we're not robbing.
we're not killing?

211
00:09:15.430 --> 00:09:16.347
What are we doing?

212
00:09:16.431 --> 00:09:17.724
DENISE: You remember
I mentioned Stuart?

213
00:09:17.807 --> 00:09:20.310
Oh. sure. How's it going? Gary.

214
00:09:20.351 --> 00:09:21.352
Hi.

215
00:09:22.353 --> 00:09:24.105
So. are you two...?

216
00:09:24.147 --> 00:09:26.274
You gotta remember.
I thought you were dead.

217
00:09:26.357 --> 00:09:28.276
Yeah. no. right. right. yeah.

218
00:09:28.359 --> 00:09:30.737
Funny story. actually. uh.
Gary was seeing my friend Lisa.

219
00:09:30.820 --> 00:09:32.322
Oh. nice girl. Yeah. Jewish.

220
00:09:32.405 --> 00:09:35.742
Yeah. and anyway. Lisa got eaten
by cannibals in Sherman Oaks.

221
00:09:35.825 --> 00:09:37.535
- Oh. no.
- DENISE: Mm-hmm.

222
00:09:37.619 --> 00:09:40.830
Human meat isn't kosher.
but I guess that only matters

223
00:09:40.914 --> 00:09:42.957
if the cannibals
are also Jewish.

224
00:09:45.585 --> 00:09:48.254
Anyway. we. um. you know.
comforted each other.

225
00:09:48.338 --> 00:09:49.964
The lady has skills. am I right?

226
00:09:50.048 --> 00:09:51.508
Well...

227
00:09:51.591 --> 00:09:55.220
To be honest. I mostly focused
on my own performance.

228
00:09:56.638 --> 00:09:58.223
Anyway. uh. we gotta go.

229
00:09:58.306 --> 00:10:00.892
Yeah. Caltech. We're on a quest.

230
00:10:00.975 --> 00:10:02.685
- ♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- There's no more Caltech.

231
00:10:02.727 --> 00:10:04.020
What's left of it
is a death trap.

232
00:10:04.062 --> 00:10:05.188
We don't have a choice.

233
00:10:05.230 --> 00:10:07.732
Yeah. an alternate version of me
came from another universe

234
00:10:07.816 --> 00:10:09.776
and explained
how I can undo the apocalypse.

235
00:10:09.859 --> 00:10:11.694
It was really cool.

236
00:10:11.778 --> 00:10:13.196
An alternate version of you?

237
00:10:13.238 --> 00:10:15.615
Yeah. same pasty face
and same whiny voice.

238
00:10:15.698 --> 00:10:17.033
It was like looking in a mirror.

239
00:10:17.117 --> 00:10:19.410
- Well. good luck.
- ♪ (MUSIC TURNS DARING) ♪

240
00:10:19.494 --> 00:10:22.580
- Yeah. nice to see you.
- Yeah. you too.

241
00:10:22.664 --> 00:10:25.625
Have fun with
the... looting and stuff.

242
