00:19:30.127 --> 00:19:32.630
(INHALES. SIGHS) ...very wonely.

483
00:19:32.713 --> 00:19:33.881
What about your harem?

484
00:19:33.923 --> 00:19:35.800
Those girls
don't really care about me.

485
00:19:35.883 --> 00:19:39.595
They're just here for the food.
medicine. free childcare.

486
00:19:39.679 --> 00:19:42.515
♪ (GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

487
00:19:43.974 --> 00:19:45.434
You know what?

488
00:19:45.476 --> 00:19:48.729
Fine. I will have dinner
with you.

489
00:19:48.813 --> 00:19:51.732
- Oh. wonderful. (CHUCKLES)
- You'll have to untie me first.

490
00:19:52.692 --> 00:19:55.361
A real relationship
is built on trust.

491
00:19:55.444 --> 00:19:56.904
That has to start now.

492
00:19:59.865 --> 00:20:03.327
Okay. (CHUCKLES)
Ooh. hey. you wike venison?

493
00:20:03.411 --> 00:20:06.455
- Mm.
- I make it with a cherwy gwaze.

494
00:20:06.539 --> 00:20:08.290
The key is low-heat weduction.

495
00:20:08.374 --> 00:20:10.292
- (GRUNTS)
- (GROANS)

496
00:20:10.334 --> 00:20:12.962
- ♪ (GROOVY MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
- (GROANS. COUGHS)

497
00:20:13.003 --> 00:20:15.631
- You are a stupid. stupid...
- (GROANS)

498
00:20:15.673 --> 00:20:18.426
...stupid. stupid. stupid man!

499
00:20:21.053 --> 00:20:24.640
(SCREAMS. GRUNTS)

500
00:20:24.724 --> 00:20:25.933
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

501
00:20:26.016 --> 00:20:27.810
(EXHALES SHARPLY. SIGHS)

502
00:20:27.893 --> 00:20:30.104
- (PANTS)
- ♪ (QUIRKY MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

503
00:20:31.021 --> 00:20:32.189
Stay healthy.

504
00:20:33.691 --> 00:20:34.942
You too!

505
00:20:35.025 --> 00:20:37.820
♪ (SENTIMENTAL MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

506
00:20:37.862 --> 00:20:39.363
- (PANTS)
- DENISE: Stuart!

507
00:20:39.447 --> 00:20:41.031
Oh. I'm so glad you're okay.

508
00:20:41.115 --> 00:20:42.158
I'm so glad you're okay.

509
00:20:42.241 --> 00:20:43.951
- (SOBS)
- (GRUNTS)

510
00:20:44.702 --> 00:20:46.036
- Uh. oh. sorry.
- DENISE: Oh!

511
00:20:46.120 --> 00:20:47.955
I'm covered with people.

512
00:20:47.997 --> 00:20:49.665
(MOCKINGLY)
Yeah. everybody's okay.

513
00:20:49.749 --> 00:20:52.543
- Let's go!
- ♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

514
00:20:54.378 --> 00:20:56.213
(SOLDIERS SCREAM)

515
00:20:57.548 --> 00:20:59.592
Thank God for geology!

516
00:20:59.675 --> 00:21:01.218
I do every day.

517
00:21:02.595 --> 00:21:04.346
- ♪ (MUSIC TURNS SUSPENSEFUL) ♪
- STUART: There it is.

518
00:21:04.388 --> 00:21:06.223
Oh. really? It looks like
one of those bread machines

519
00:21:06.307 --> 00:21:07.224
from Williams Sonoma.

520
00:21:07.308 --> 00:21:10.352
It's a vari-state
quantum interference device!

521
00:21:10.436 --> 00:21:12.104
Mm. Could be both.

522
00:21:12.188 --> 00:21:13.981
- Can you fix it?
- Yes. I think so.

523
00:21:14.023 --> 00:21:15.858
- (DEVICE RUMBLES)
- Oh. calibration is off.

524
00:21:15.941 --> 00:21:17.693
- Gotta reconfigure.
- (DEVICE BEEPS)

525
00:21:17.777 --> 00:21:19.153
Change the inputs.

526
00:21:19.236 --> 00:21:20.613
BERT: What's supposed
to happen?

527
00:21:20.696 --> 00:21:23.073
- (DEVICE CHIRPS. HUMS)
- Does everything just go back
to the way it was?

528
00:21:23.157 --> 00:21:25.034
Yeah. fingers crossed.

529
00:21:25.075 --> 00:21:27.161
That would mean you and I
would be together again.

530
00:21:27.244 --> 00:21:29.371
Slow down. champ.
I'm still grieving.

531
00:21:29.413 --> 00:21:30.581
STUART: Hmm. hmm.

532
00:21:30.664 --> 00:21:33.209
- I think I got it!
- ♪ (TRIUMPHANT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

533
00:21:33.250 --> 00:21:34.668
(GROANS)

534
00:21:34.752 --> 00:21:36.504
